<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="588" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,512,539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be easily distinguished from its two congeners by the body generally black except sixth and seventh abdominal segments and female genitalia dull yellow, the post-antennal protuberance being high and spine-shaped, the humeral angles of the pronotum beng more obtuse, and the tip of fore tibia produced into a sharp spine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="592" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,435,656,683]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Description. Colour</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[448,550,657,683]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 2–5" captionStart-1="FIGURES 6–9" captionStartId-0="3.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,264,1964,1989]" captionTargetBox-0="[185,1402,193,1942]" captionTargetBox-1="[200,1385,185,1927]" captionTargetId-0="figure@3.[173,1414,181,1948]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[196,1390,181,1938]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="FIGURES 2–5. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 2–3, head and pronotum; 4, foreleg; 5, left hemelytron; 2, 5, dorsal view; 3, 4, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 2, 3, 5; 1.5 mm for Fig. 4." captionText-1="FIGURES 6–9. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 6–7, abdomen; 8–9, apical part of abdomen. 6, ventral view; 7, ventrolateral view; 8, lateral view; 9, posteroventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 6, 7; 0.3 mm for Figs 8, 9." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855232" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855234" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3855232/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3855234/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Figs 2–9</figureCitation>
). Body generally black, dorsal connexiva of fifth and sixth segments and female genitalia dull yellow. First antennal segment, head, rostrum, pronotum, scutellum, coxae, femora and tibiae, corium, dorsal connexiva of second to fifth segments, second to fourth abdominal segments and most of fifth abdominal segment (except small yellow portion) dark brown to black. Second and third antennal segments, apical part of third visible rostral segment, trochanters and tarsi, and a longitudinal area between Cu and PCu veins of hemelytra pale brown. The sixth and seventh abdominal segments (including connexiva) and the genital segments dull yellow. Small scattered hairy patches on corium white. Eyes grayish, ocellus whitish, spot between ocelli yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,908,935]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Structure.</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[400,498,909,935]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1927,1952]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox-0="[153,1424,188,1885]" captionTargetBox-1="[185,1402,193,1942]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[173,1414,181,1948]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 3 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 2–5. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 2–3, head and pronotum; 4, foreleg; 5, left hemelytron; 2, 5, dorsal view; 3, 4, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 2, 3, 5; 1.5 mm for Fig. 4." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855230" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855232" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3855230/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3855232/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Figs 1–3</figureCitation>
) elongate elliptical, covered by somewhat oblique short setae, head subequal to pronotum in length, 4.2 times as long as width across eyes; anteocular portion 0.6 times as long as postocular portion, interocular furrow almost straight; with a pair of post-antennal protuberance long, spine-shaped, directed anterolaterad (
<figureCitation box="[214,314,1017,1043]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1927,1952]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox-0="[153,1424,188,1885]" captionTargetBox-1="[185,1402,193,1942]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[173,1414,181,1948]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 3 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 2–5. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 2–3, head and pronotum; 4, foreleg; 5, left hemelytron; 2, 5, dorsal view; 3, 4, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 2, 3, 5; 1.5 mm for Fig. 4." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855230" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855232" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3855230/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3855232/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Figs 1–3</figureCitation>
); eyes (
<figureCitation box="[399,497,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[173,1414,181,1948]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 2–3, head and pronotum; 4, foreleg; 5, left hemelytron; 2, 5, dorsal view; 3, 4, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 2, 3, 5; 1.5 mm for Fig. 4." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855232" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855232/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Figs 2, 3</figureCitation>
) medium sized, not reaching level of ventral surface of head, approximately as wide as interocular space in dorsal view (0.9: 1), ocelli small and widely separated. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1218,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1927,1952]" captionTargetBox="[153,1424,188,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855230/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) slender; segments I–III covered by somewhat short, curved, suberect setae, segment IV furnished with short, reclining setae; segment I longest, longer than head and pronotum together in length (1.2: 1); proportion of segments I to IV 2.1: 0.7: 1.5: 1; labium (
<figureCitation box="[245,312,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[173,1414,181,1948]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 2–3, head and pronotum; 4, foreleg; 5, left hemelytron; 2, 5, dorsal view; 3, 4, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 2, 3, 5; 1.5 mm for Fig. 4." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855232" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855232/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) covered by short suberect setae; first visible labial segment thickest, straight and longest, 1.8 time as long as length of second and distinctly extending beyond posterior margin of eyes; third labial segment shortest and reaching thorax; proportion of visible labial segments I to III 3.6: 1.8: 1.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[324,422,1269,1295]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1927,1952]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox-0="[153,1424,188,1885]" captionTargetBox-1="[185,1402,193,1942]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[173,1414,181,1948]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 3 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 2–5. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 2–3, head and pronotum; 4, foreleg; 5, left hemelytron; 2, 5, dorsal view; 3, 4, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 2, 3, 5; 1.5 mm for Fig. 4." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855230" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855232" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3855230/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3855232/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Figs 1–3</figureCitation>
) covered with short suberect setae; length subequal to width across humeri (0.9: 1); anterolateral angle short and conical; anterior lobe of pronotum approximately 0.6 times as long as its maximum width, with glabrous impression, anterior part with a shallow, middle part with a deep longitudinal sulcus, subbasal part with a pair of distinct protuberances; posterior lobe approximately 0.5 times as long as humeral width, 1.7 times as long as anterior lobe; posterior lobe of pronotum bulged, deeply rugose, discal part somewhat flat, humeral angles obtuse and slightly prominent; postolateral margin nearly straight and horizontal, posterior margin slightly convex. Scutellum approximately 0.56 times as long as maximum width of its exposed part, with a “V”-shaped carina, apical part rounded (
<figureCitation box="[308,379,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1927,1952]" captionTargetBox="[153,1424,188,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855230/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[393,410,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[173,1414,181,1948]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 2–3, head and pronotum; 4, foreleg; 5, left hemelytron; 2, 5, dorsal view; 3, 4, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 2, 3, 5; 1.5 mm for Fig. 4." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855232" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855232/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
Forelegs (
<figureCitation box="[310,380,1557,1583]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1927,1952]" captionTargetBox="[153,1424,188,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855230/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[394,409,1557,1583]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[173,1414,181,1948]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 2–3, head and pronotum; 4, foreleg; 5, left hemelytron; 2, 5, dorsal view; 3, 4, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 2, 3, 5; 1.5 mm for Fig. 4." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855232" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855232/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">4</figureCitation>
) furnished with short, reclining or suberect setae, margin with short, dense setae; fore femur thickened, basal half distinctly incurved; femur 5.7 times as long as coxa, 8.3 times as long as trochanter, 6.0 times as long as its maximum width; fore tibiae 1.1 times as long as femur, strongly bent inward apically, and with a sharp spine on tip (
<figureCitation box="[297,366,1665,1691]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,193,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[173,1414,181,1948]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–5. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 2–3, head and pronotum; 4, foreleg; 5, left hemelytron; 2, 5, dorsal view; 3, 4, lateral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 2, 3, 5; 1.5 mm for Fig. 4." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855232" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855232/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); tarsus two-segmented, 0.08 times as long as tibia. Maximum width of mid femur smaller than that of fore femur (0.4: 1); length of mid femur subequal to length of mid tibia (1: 1.1); maximum width of hind femur smaller than that of fore femur (0.3: 1), length of hind femur smaller than that of hind tibia (0.8: 1); femora and tibiae with short setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[323,393,1809,1835]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1927,1952]" captionTargetBox="[153,1424,188,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855230/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[406,448,1809,1835]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1964,1989]" captionTargetBox="[200,1385,185,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[196,1390,181,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–9. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. 6–7, abdomen; 8–9, apical part of abdomen. 6, ventral view; 7, ventrolateral view; 8, lateral view; 9, posteroventral view. Scale bars: 1 mm for Figs 6, 7; 0.3 mm for Figs 8, 9." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855234/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">6, 7</figureCitation>
) dilated, approximately twice as long as its maximum width, wider than maximum width of hemelytra in rest; abdominal segments III, IV, V and VI subequal in length (proportions from III to VI as 1.02: 1.08: 1.05: 1.00); dorsal connexivum moderately dilated, especially fourth to sixth segments. Hemelytra (
<figureCitation box="[1358,1429,1881,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1927,1952]" captionTargetBox="[153,1424,188,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rihirbus kronganaensis sp. nov., female. Scale bar: 3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3855230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3855230/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
